It’s day 5, the last post of my #vinyasasadhana challenge with #loveofashtanga!

Urdvha Dhanurasana 

Letting Go

Practice is the effort we make to still the mind. But this is only half the equation of yoga. The other half is non-attachment. 

The beauty of the vinyasa system is that it is a technique to realize both practice and non-attachment. Practice asks us to focus and manifest. Non-attachment requires us to accept the results of our efforts, whatever they may be.

I have found that the best way to process thoughts and feelings in my meditation practice is to focus on structure and technique. I do my best to maintain the Asana and flow through the vinyasa, regardless of whatever thoughts and feelings might arise. Of course, it’s a challenge, and I’m not always successful 😅, but just the effort itself is liberating. 

How do you find non-attachment in your own Sadhana?

