Virabhadrasana A and B

Precision
Physical precision is embodied focus. The vinyasa Sadhana is very precise in its coordinates for vinyasa and Asana, providing us with many opportunities to practice mindful precision.

I’ve chosen the Virabhadrasana sequence because it’s all about mindful precision. In the vinyasa from Virabhadrasana A to B, my teacher always says “Don’t change your legs!” The foot and leg position remains the same, which means you need to step long enough in A to be properly positioned in B.

Try your best to place your feet and hands where they need to be the first time you put them into position. Be mindful of additional movements that you may be adding into practice to compensate for a lack of precision.

