Utkatasana

Sameness
Sama, or Sameness, is a quality of steadiness that we can manifest in our vinyasa Sadhana. It is relaxed effort that is evenly applied in practice.

To practice this technique, treat each vinyasa as equally important. Try not to prioritize fancy moves over the breath and the vinyasa count. 

For example, in Ashtanga the vinyasa from Downward Facing Dog into Utkatasana is all
on one inhalation.  There’s no time or breath for shitty gymnastics when we follow the traditional count.

Watch the quality of movement and breath in each vinyasa. What can you do to energize it more? What effort can you reduce?

