It’s day 2 of my #vinyasasadhana challenge with #loveofashtanga!

Trikonasana A & B

Straight Lines 📐 
The Ashtanga Sadhana is a structured sequence of asana linked together with vinyasa. When practicing vinyasa, we can reveal unnecessary and/or habitual movements by moving through the vinyasa in the straightest line possible. 

Of course, sometimes we need to take extra  breaths and movements to get into a posture, and that’s totally fine. But it’s always useful to check in and see if the extra movement actually needs to be there, and if it doesn’t, can we let it go?

Using Ashtanga’s traditional vinyasa structure, try to move through your vinyasa using the straightest and simplest lines possible.

